    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "From the way I'm using it and understanding it, kind of, yes. The main difference being that `debug_traceTransaction` is called on a mined tx, whereas this function is called as the function is executed, for each op code.\r\n\r\nThe big upside is memory usage as it doesn't have to load the entire trace, the big downside imo is that there is no way to reliably match a call of this function with the corresponding tx hash (as it doesn't exist yet when it's called). ",
